You have discovered that the sun is based on the same principles as other stars: It was discovered that the activity of all stars in the system is driven by their luminosity, rotation, and nothing else.
In order to determine the Rossby number of a star, which is related to the plasma stream, the luminosity and the rotation are taken into account together.
The smaller the Rossby number is, the less active the star is in terms of reversals of the magnetic field.
