The 802.11n-Standard runs on the frequencies 2,4 Ghz as well as 5,0 Ghz.
Thus, it can be backward compatible with 802.11a, 802.11b and 802.11g, provided the base station has dual-radio.
The speed of 802.11n is considerably faster than that of its predecessors, which had a maximum theoretical throughput of 600 Mbit/s.
